The paper deals with algorithms for solving hard lattice problems, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as cryptography (cs.CR), information theory (cs.IT), and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also involves techniques for near neighbor searching on dense data sets, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
